1. Obtain cell leakage power from liberty files using one of the following methods:
  - If the cell group has the cell_leakage_power attribute, its value will be taken as the cell leakage power in one PVT corner.
  - If the cell group does not have the cell_leakage_power attribute, Liberate will take the value of the value attribute from the first leakage_power group that does not have the when attribute as the cell leakage power.
  - Otherwise, Liberate will skip generating scaling factors group for this cell with a warning message *Warning* (merge_leakage) : cannot determine the leakage_power value for the cell. 
 cell (AN2DP) {
 cell_leakage_power : 0.000491; 
 area : 10467;
 cell_footprint : "an2d2"; 
 leakage_power () {
 value : 36.34567;
 related_pg_pin : VDD;
} 
 leakage_power () {
 value : 20.623454;
 when : "!A1 !A2 !Z";
 related_pg_pin : VDD;
}
2. Library characterization - there are two use models for performing library characterization. These are:
  - when liberty files are present for all corners, use the following use model to generate the merged library file with the leakage scale factor table:
  - read all P*V*T library files using the read_library command
  - generate leakage scale factor table with the PVT information using the merge_leakage command 
 A sample script is shown below: 
 read_library { \
 SS_1.0_25.lib SS_1.0_85.lib SS_1.0_125.lib \
 SS_1.2_25.lib SS_1.2_85.lib SS_1.2_125.lib \
 TT_1.0_25.lib TT_1.0_85.lib TT_1.0_125.lib \
 TT_1.2_25.lib TT_1.2_85.lib TT_1.2_125.lib \
}
merge_leakage -process {SS TT} \
 -voltage {1.0 1.2 } \
 -temp {25 85 125 } \
 -base {TT 1.0 25}
write_library -ecsm ecsm.lib
  - when liberty files are not present for all corners, use the following use model to generate the merged library file with the leakage scale factor table:
  - Generate scaling library file for each process separately based on V*T
  - Merge these scaling library files using the merge_library command 
